				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>lua</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:70px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="inline" style="margin-bottom:-60px">
<code data-language="lua">lua{options}(-- line of Lua code)
lua{options}
{
	-- block of Lua code
}</code></pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:70px">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="inline" style="margin-bottom:-60px">
<code data-language="lua">\@lua{options}(-- line of Lua code)
\@lua{options}
{
	-- block of Lua code
}</code></pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>lua</mono> function is for running <mono>Lua</mono> code, it takes zero parameters with the call followed by a block of <mono>Lua</mono> code otherwise a single parameter that should be the code to run. See <a href="@pathtopage(docs/lua)">here</a> for more information about <mono>Lua</mono>.
				</p>

				<h4 id="options">
					Options
				</h4>
				<p>
					The following options are available for <mono>lua</mono> calls:

					<center class="table">
						<table id="Lua_options_table" class="alt">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>option</th>
									<th>description</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>!o</mono></td>
								<td>do not return result</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>o</mono></td>
								<td>return result</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>pb</mono></td>
								<td>parse block with language call is made from before running code with <mono>Lua</mono></td>
							</tr>
							<tfoot>
								<tr>
									<th>option</th>
									<th>description</th>
								</tr>
							</tfoot>
						</table>
					</center>
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Examples of <mono>lua</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
lua
{
	local vips = require "vips"

	local image = vips.Image.new_from_file("logo.png")
	image:resize(0.5):webpsave("logo.webp")
}</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>lua</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
\@lua
{
	local vips = require "vips"

	local image = vips.Image.new_from_file("logo.png")
	image:resize(0.5):webpsave("logo.webp")
}</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
